υ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νυμφόδωρος\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Νυμφόδωρος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Νυμφόδωρος\">ΝΥ[.....]ΡΟΣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἀρχαγάθου\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἀρχαγάθου\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Ἀρχαγάθου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Ἀρχαγάθος\">ΑΡ[.....]ΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">ΤΟΥ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Νυμφόδωρος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Νυμφόδωρος\">ΝΥΜΦΟΔΩΡΟΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Ἀρχαγάθου\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"Ἀρχαγάθος\">ΑΡΧΑΓΑΘΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τοῦ\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"ὁ\">ΤΟΥ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text after Kaibel in IG, following the conjectural restoraiton of Franz in CIG\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0981-2465\">Matthew Hewitt\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Ny[mphodo]ros, son of Ar[chagath]os...\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>We are dependent entirely upon the antiquarian record, which suggests this is two non-joining but related fragments of a marble stone. It is impossible to know therefore whether it was true marble, or a polishable limestone, and whether it was a public or a private (i.e. likely funerary) inscription, since it appears to contain traces of perhaps two names.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5590 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">330\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>'litterae elegantes' (Muenter)\u003C/p> Line 1    Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[192,195,198,201,204,207,210,213],{"id":193,"html":194},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Matthew Hewitt\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Νυμφόδωρος\n                    Ἀρχαγάθου\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νυμφόδωρος\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Νυμφόδωρος\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Νυμφόδωρος\">Νυ[μφόδω?]ρος\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname